snippet.title: LISA - DREAM feat. Kentaro Sakaguchi (Official Short Film MV)
snippet.description:
LISA‚Äôs debut album, ‚ÄòAlter Ego‚Äô is out now. Listen here: https://lisa.lnk.to/AlterEgo

Lyrics:
I‚Äôve been thinking 
That I got no idea what you‚Äôre thinking 
Are you happy? Are you sad?
Are you always gonna hate me for that night in Tokyo? 
When it ended 
I kinda hoped that it‚Äôd be open ended
But you never looked back 
Well I guess you can‚Äôt hold on to something once you let it go 
But I know a place 
Where we can be us
I know it ain‚Äôt real 
But it‚Äôs real enough 
From sun going down to sun coming up 
It‚Äôs like you‚Äôre here with me 
Whenever I close my eyes
It‚Äôs taking me back in time
Been drowning in dreams lately 
Like it‚Äôs 2019 baby 
Whenever I‚Äôm missing you 
Call you up but I can‚Äôt get through
Don‚Äôt know where you sleep lately 
But I‚Äôll see you in my dreams maybe 
We can catch up, drive down our old street
If all that we were is all that we‚Äôll ever be
It‚Äôs bittersweet
At least a girl can dream 
I guess that I‚Äôm taking what I can get 
‚ÄòCause I don‚Äôt get nothing new from your friends 
If you got the harder side of the break 
Then why is it harder for me to take 
There‚Äôs so much I might never get to say, ay
But I know a place 
Where we can be us
I know it ain‚Äôt real 
But it‚Äôs real enough 
From sun going down to sun coming up 
It‚Äôs like you‚Äôre here with me 
Whenever I close my eyes
It‚Äôs taking me back in time
Been drowning in dreams lately 
Like it‚Äôs 2019 baby 
Whenever I‚Äôm missing you 
Call you up but I can‚Äôt get through
Don‚Äôt know where you sleep lately 
But I‚Äôll see you in my dreams maybe 
We can catch up, drive down our old street
If all that we were is all that we‚Äôll ever be
It‚Äôs bittersweet
At least a girl can dream 
I-I-I know it‚Äôs only in my mind
Playing three nights on the stereo
Like a movie scene, DiCaprio 
Oh l-I-I put my make up on just to fall asleep
It‚Äôs like you‚Äôre here with me 
Whenever I close my eyes
It‚Äôs taking me back in time
Been drowning in dreams lately 
Like it‚Äôs 2019 baby 
Whenever I‚Äôm missing you 
Call you up but I can‚Äôt get through
Don‚Äôt know where you sleep lately 
But I‚Äôll see you in my dreams maybe 
We can catch up, drive down our old street
If all that we were is something we‚Äôll never be
It‚Äôs bittersweet
Can we be friends at least

snippet.title: OG vs NG: Legacies Clash | Day 1
snippet.description:
History. Rivalry. Glory. 
This is OG vs NG #legaciesclash, where the titans of the old generation go head-to-head with the fearless new generation in a battle that will define BGMI‚Äôs future. 

The OGs: battle-hardened legends who built the legacy. 
The NGs: unstoppable young guns hungry to rewrite it. 

From jaw-dropping clutches to savage mind games, every round is a statement. Every fight is a chance to prove who truly rules the battleground. 

Two eras collide. Only one will walk away in control.

About YRF Spy Universe:
YRF Spy Universe is a first of its kind cinematic universe of spy thriller films in India. The first film in the universe, "Ek Tha Tiger", starring Salman Khan and Katrina Kaif was released in 2012, followed by its sequel "Tiger Zinda Hai" in 2017. The third film in the universe, "War" was released in 2019 and starred Hrithik Roshan and Tiger Shroff in pivotal roles. "Pathaan" was the fourth instalment in the Spy Universe franchise which was released in 2023 starring Shah Rukh Khan, Deepika Padukone and John Abraham. "Tiger 3", the fifth instalment in the YRF Spy Universe and the third film in the Tiger series, starring Salman Khan, Katrina Kaif and Emraan Hashmi, released in 2023. "War 2" is the sixth film of the YRF Spy Universe franchise and will release on 14 August 2025. The film stars two of the greatest cinematic icons Hrithik Roshan and NTR, with Kiara Advani in the lead and is directed by Ayan Mukerji. ‚ÄúAlpha‚Äù, the seventh instalment in the franchise and Hindi cinema's first female-led YRF Spy Universe film, starring Alia Bhatt and Sharvari, is set to release on 25 December 2025.

snippet.description:

Star Cast: Dilip Kumar, Nutan, Naseeruddin Shah, Jackie Shroff, Anil Kapoor, Anupam Kher, Sridevi, Poonam Dhillon
Singers: Mohammad Aziz, Kavita Krishnamurthy
Music Director:  Laxmikant Pyarelal
Lyrics by: Anand Bakshi
Producer & Director: Subhash Ghai

Mera Karma Tu Mera Dharma Tu 
Tera Sab Kuch Main Mera Sab Kuch Tu
Har Karam Apna Karenge
Har Karam Apna Karenge Aye Watan Tere Liye
Dil Diya Hai Jaan Bhi Denge Aye Watan Tere Liye
Har Karam Apna Karenge Aye Watan Tere Liye
Dil Diya Hai Jaan Bhi Denge Aye Watan Tere Liye
Har Karam Apna Karenge Aye Watan Tere Liye

Aye Watan Mehboob Mere Tujhpe Dil Kurban Hai
Aye Watan Mehboob Mere Tujhpe Dil Kurban Hai
Hum Jiyenge Aur Marenge Aye Watan Tere Liye
Dil Diya Hai Jaan Bhi Denge Aye Watan Tere Liye
Dil Diya Hai Jaan Bhi Denge Aye Watan Tere Liye

Hindu Muslim Sikh Isayi Hum Watan Hum Naam Hai

Jo Kare Inko Juda Mazhab Nahi Ilzam Hai
Hum Jiyenge Aur Marenge Aye Watan Tere Liye
Dil Diya Hai Jaan Bhi Denge Aye Watan Tere Liye
Dil Diya Hai Jaan Bhi Denge Aye Watan Tere Liye

Teri Galiyon Mein Chala Kar Nafraton Ki Goliya
Loot Te Hai Kuch Lutere Dulhano Ki Doliyan

Khelte Hai Bekhabar Apne Lahu Se Holiya
Hum Jiyenge Aur Marenge Aye Watan Tere Liye

About YRF Spy Universe:
YRF Spy Universe is a first of its kind cinematic universe of spy thriller films in India. The first film in the universe, "Ek Tha Tiger", starring Salman Khan and Katrina Kaif was released in 2012, followed by its sequel "Tiger Zinda Hai" in 2017. The third film in the universe, "War" was released in 2019 and starred Hrithik Roshan and Tiger Shroff in pivotal roles. "Pathaan" was the fourth instalment in the Spy Universe franchise which was released in 2023 starring Shah Rukh Khan, Deepika Padukone and John Abraham. "Tiger 3", the fifth instalment in the YRF Spy Universe and the third film in the Tiger series, starring Salman Khan, Katrina Kaif and Emraan Hashmi, released in 2023. "War 2" is the sixth film of the YRF Spy Universe franchise and will release on 14 August 2025. The film stars two of the greatest cinematic icons Hrithik Roshan and NTR, with Kiara Advani in the lead and is directed by Ayan Mukerji. ‚ÄúAlpha‚Äù, the seventh instalment in the franchise and Hindi cinema's first female-led YRF Spy Universe film, starring Alia Bhatt and Sharvari, is set to release on 25 December 2025.

Trailer mashups are often created for a movie that does not exist now or to change the genre of an existing film. These are derivative works and as such, may find protection from copyright claims under the doctrine of fair use. The trailer mashups are not only a user-generated form of digital creativity but a way to create anticipation for future releases, working in tandem with current movie trailers. Movie trailers are designed to give minimal plot detail and to create hype and anticipation. Fan-made trailer mashups allow the audience to perform their own cinematic spin on current movie footage. The Great Shinobi War  | Academy Trials Day 1 #freefire #gyangaming #freefirelive 

Schedule
Date : 14 AUG 2025
IDP Time : 08:00 PM 
START Time : 08:10 PM

Participating Teams :

GROUP KONOHAGAKURE

NG PROS
KV18 ESPORTS 
VASIYO ESPORTS 
RNX ESPORTS 
DESI ESPORTS 
SARKAR
TEAM ELITE
RG ARMY
Ahmed Gaming
Ebuus Era
EG OFFICIALS 
FULL MOON



Prizepool - 10,000 INR
Team Distribution & Grouping

48 Total Teams:

- 24 from Partner Program
- 12 from Extended Program
- 12 from Open Qualifiers

4 Groups of 12 Teams each:

- Konohagakure (Hidden Leaf Village)
- Sunagakure (Hidden Sand Village)
- Kirigakure (Hidden Mist Village)
- Kumogakure (Hidden Cloud Village)

Tournament Format & Roadmap


Stages & Details:

Academy Trials

- 4 Groups (12 teams each)
- 6 matches per group
- Top 6 teams from each group qualify


Ninja Vanguard

- 2 Groups (12 teams each)
- 6 matches per group
- Top 6 teams from each group qualify


Great Shinobi War (Grand Finals)

- 12 Final teams
- 12 matches in a 1-day grand final
- Winner crowned champion


Shinobi Reckoning (Clash Squad Showdown)

- Top 8 teams from Grand Finals
- Quarterfinals: Best of 1 matches
- Semifinals: Best of 3 matches
- Finals: Best of 5 matches

Tournament Timeline

- Day 1 (14 August): Academy Trials ‚Äì Group Konohagakure (Hidden Leaf Village)
- Day 2 (15 August): Academy Trials ‚Äì Group Sunagakure (Hidden Sand Village)
- Day 3 (16 August): Academy Trials ‚Äì Group Kirigakure (Hidden Mist Village)
- Day 4 (17 August): Academy Trials ‚Äì Group Kumogakure (Hidden Cloud Village)
- Day 5 (18 August): Ninja Vanguard ‚Äì Group A
- Day 6 (19 August): Ninja Vanguard ‚Äì Group B
- Day 7 (20 August): Great Shinobi War ‚Äì Grand Finals
- Day 8 (21 August): Shinobi Reckoning ‚Äì Clash Squad Showdown

Prize Pool Distribution

Total Prize Pool: 3,00,000 Diamonds

- Champion: 1,20,000 Diamonds
- Runner-Up: 50,000 Diamonds
- Second Runner-Up: 30,000 Diamonds
- Most Valuable Player (MVP): 20,000 Diamonds
- Clash Squad Winner: 80,000 Diamonds
